<div><div><h2>Reporter's Take | What The Top-Level Resignations At Yes Bank Mean</h2></div><div>"independent director r chandrashekhar's resignation from the board of yes bank is the latest in the series of top executives exiting the private bank. last week non-executive chairman ashok chawla and another independent director vasant gujarathi left the private sector lender.in a bse filing the bank stated that chandrashekhar resigned due to personal reasons. however according to sources it was yes bank's decision to overhaul its board that drove him out.m saraswathy gets in conversation with moneycontrol's beena parmar to discuss the recent resignations of top executives at yes bank promoter's plans to overhaul the bank's board and potential replacements for the outgoing ceo rana kapoor."</div></div>